Section 325.20. A. All mobile food preparation vehicles
17
18
operating within this state prior to July 1, 2024, that are capable
18
19
of producing smoke or grease-laden vapors shall be in compliance
19
20
with the most current adopted fire code that was in effect at the
20
21
time of the most recent inspection of the mobile food preparation
21
22
vehicle. The vehicle shall remain in compliance with such fire code
22
23
for a period of ten (10) years from the date of the most recent
23
24
inspection. At the expiration of the ten-year period, a subsequent
24
